==English==

===Etymology===
Short for ''Canterbury pace'', from the supposed easy pace of medieval pilgrims to Canterbury.

===Pronunciation===
*[[w:International Phonetic Alphabet|IPA]]:/kæntɛr/, /kæntər/

===Noun===
'''canter'''
# A [[pace]] of a [[horse]] between a [[trot]] and a [[gallop]], with not less than one foot on the ground at any time.
# A [[ride]] on a horse at such speed.

===Verb===
'''to canter'''
# Move at such pace.

====Derived terms====
*[[in a canter]] (or [[at a canter]])